{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SmWMn6T1rXa4YJqJ7NwKx1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→import java.util.HashSet;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Digits;\n    14→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    16→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model.Person;\n    17→\n    18→@Entity\n    19→@Table(name = \"owners\")\n    20→public class Owner extends Person {\n    21→\n    22→    @Column(name = \"address\")\n    23→    @NotEmpty\n    24→    @FormParam(\"address\")\n    25→    public String address;\n    26→\n    27→    @Column(name = \"city\")\n    28→    @NotEmpty\n    29→    @FormParam(\"city\")\n    30→    public String city;\n    31→\n    32→    @Column(name = \"telephone\")\n    33→    @NotEmpty\n    34→    @Digits(fraction = 0, integer = 10)\n    35→    @FormParam(\"telephone\")\n    36→    public String telephone;\n    37→\n    38→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"owner\", fetch = FetchType.EAGER) // it is eager but probably it could be changed to lazy and make some lazy load before rendering template but we might end up in similar performance\n    39→    public Set<Pet> pets;\n    40→\n    41→    public static Collection<Owner> findByLastName(String name) {\n    42→        return Owner.list(\"lastName\", name);\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public Owner attach() {\n    46→        return getEntityManager().merge(this);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    public String toString() {\n    51→        return \"Owner [address=\" + address + \", city=\" + city + \", pets=\" + pets + \", telephone=\" + telephone + \"]\";\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public void addPet(Pet pet) {\n    55→        getPetsInternal().add(pet);\n    56→        pet.owner = this;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    protected Set<Pet> getPetsInternal() {\n    60→\t\tif (this.pets == null) {\n    61→\t\t\tthis.pets = new HashSet<>();\n    62→\t\t}\n    63→\t\treturn this.pets;\n    64→\t}\n    65→\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UQadJPK58QmuyaAvhgm3WQ","session_id":"52be45b4-0245-40cb-9c77-3e6f169390e0","uuid":"65dcb446-a121-4446-9437-482cd0dbc0fd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UQadJPK58QmuyaAvhgm3WQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, I'll summarize my findings comprehensively:\n\n🔍 Comprehensive Codebase Overview: Quarkus Pet Clinic Application\n\n1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n--------------------\nA Quarkus-based implementation of the classic Spring Pet Clinic application, with the following key characteristics:\n- Java 21 \n- Maven-based build\n- Quarkus 3.30.5 framework\n- PostgreSQL database (with H2 for dev/test)\n\n2. DIRECTORY TREE\n-----------------\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__spring/run_2/output\n├── Dockerfile\n├── pom.xml\n└── src\n    ├── main\n    │   ├── docker\n    │   │   └── Dockerfiles (multiple variants)\n    │   ├── java\n    │   │   └── org/quarkus/samples/petclinic\n    │   │       ├── model\n    │   │       ├── owner\n    │   │       ├── system\n    │   │       ├── vet\n    │   │       └── visit\n    │   ├── kubernetes\n    │   │   └── deployment configurations\n    │   ├── resources\n    │   │   ├── templates (HTML)\n    │   │   ├── META-INF/resources\n    │   │   │   ├── fonts\n    │   │   │   └── images\n    │   │   └── scss\n    │   └── scss (stylesheets)\n    └── test\n        └── java (integration and unit tests)\n\n3. KEY TECHNICAL COMPONENTS\n---------------------------\n- Framework: Quarkus\n- ORM: Hibernate with Panache\n- Database: PostgreSQL (production), H2 (dev/test)\n- REST: JAX-RS\n- Templating: Qute\n- Validation: Hibernate Validator\n- Containerization: Jib\n- Deployment: Kubernetes support\n\n4. DATABASE CONFIGURATION\n------------------------\n- Dev/Test: H2 in-memory database\n- Production: PostgreSQL\n- Seed data loaded from import.sql\n- Hibernate ORM configured with different profile-specific settings\n\n5. BUILD CONFIGURATION (pom.xml highlights)\n-------------------------------------------\n- Java 21\n- Quarkus 3.30.5\n- Key dependencies:\n  * quarkus-rest\n  * quarkus-rest-jackson\n  * quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache\n  * quarkus-jdbc-postgresql\n  * quarkus-container-image-jib\n  * quarkus-kubernetes\n\n6. CONTAINERIZATION\n------------------\n- Dockerfile uses maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble base image\n- Installs Python, uv, playwright\n- Builds application during image creation\n- Runs Quarkus JAR with dev profile\n\n7. MAIN PACKAGES\n----------------\n- org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model: Base model classes\n- org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner: Owner, Pet, Visit management\n- org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet: Veterinarian management\n- org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system: System-level resources and utilities\n\n8. KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n---------------------\n- Repository pattern via Panache\n- REST resources for each domain object\n- Form-based interactions\n- Validation via annotations\n- Internationalization support\n\n9. TESTING\n----------\n- Unit tests for resources\n- Integration tests \n- Uses JUnit 5 and REST Assured\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the codebase?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52be45b4-0245-40cb-9c77-3e6f169390e0","uuid":"90dbf129-417b-41e4-9ad6-5cd8db86281a"}
