{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TZc9UHZ4moNsxzityt1STQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→<table id=\"owners\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→        <tr>\n     8→            <th style=\"width: 150px;\">{msg:name}</th>\n     9→            <th style=\"width: 200px;\">{msg:address}</th>\n    10→            <th>City</th>\n    11→            <th style=\"width: 120px\">{msg:telephone}</th>\n    12→            <th>{msg:pets}</th>\n    13→        </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tbody>\n    16→        {#for owner in owners}\n    17→        <tr>\n    18→            <td>\n    19→                <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}\"/>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</a>\n    20→            </td>\n    21→            <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    22→            <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→            <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    24→            <td>\n    25→                {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    26→                    <span>{pet.name}</span>\n    27→                {/for}\n    28→            </td>\n    29→        </tr>\n    30→        {/for}\n    31→    </tbody>\n    32→</table>\n    33→{/body}\n    34→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52be45b4-0245-40cb-9c77-3e6f169390e0","uuid":"14a8a003-6eae-4fb1-8ee7-f20dfb62965b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NEsU4CqEMGpTtmF9rkRvi8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→<h2>Owner Information</h2>\n     4→  \n     5→  \n     6→    <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th>{msg:name}</th>\n     9→        <td><b>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</b></td>\n    10→      </tr>\n    11→      <tr>\n    12→        <th>{msg:address}</th>\n    13→        <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    14→      </tr>\n    15→      <tr>\n    16→        <th>{msg:city}</th>\n    17→        <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    18→      </tr>\n    19→      <tr>\n    20→        <th>{msg:telephone}</th>\n    21→        <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    22→      </tr>\n    23→    </table>\n    24→  \n    25→    <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/edit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Edit\n    26→      Owner</a>\n    27→    <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/new\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Add\n    28→      New Pet</a>\n    29→  \n    30→    <br />\n    31→    <br />\n    32→    <br />\n    33→    {#if owner.pets}\n    34→    <h2>{msg:pets_and_visits}</h2>\n    35→  \n    36→    <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    37→        \n    38→      {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    39→      <tr>\n    40→        <td valign=\"top\">\n    41→          <dl class=\"dl-horizontal\">\n    42→            <dt>{msg:name}</dt>\n    43→            <dd>{pet.name}</dd>\n    44→            <dt>{msg:birthdate}</dt>\n    45→            <dd>{pet.birthDate.format()}</dd>\n    46→            <dt>{msg:type}</dt>\n    47→            <dd>{pet.type.stringify}</dd>\n    48→          </dl>\n    49→        </td>\n    50→        <td valign=\"top\">\n    51→          <table class=\"table-condensed\">\n    52→            <thead>\n    53→              <tr>\n    54→                <th>{msg:visit_date}</th>\n    55→                <th>{msg:description}</th>\n    56→              </tr>\n    57→              <tr>\n    58→                <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/edit\">{msg:edit_pet}</a></td>\n    59→                <td><a\n    60→                  href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/visits/new\">{msg:add_visit}</a></td>\n    61→              </tr>\n    62→            </thead>\n    63→            {#for visit in pet.sortedVisits}\n    64→            <tr>\n    65→              <td>{visit.date.format()}</td>\n    66→              <td>{visit.description ?: ''}</td>\n    67→            </tr>\n    68→            {/for}\n    69→          </table>\n    70→        </td>\n    71→      </tr>\n    72→      {/for}\n    73→  \n    74→    </table>\n    75→    {/if}\n    76→    {/body}\n    77→    {/include}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52be45b4-0245-40cb-9c77-3e6f169390e0","uuid":"65a348da-76dd-40c8-9385-797b3c1e883e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FzDSA1B4oQvqXjAZPXNcg3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>{msg:owner}</h2>\n     4→<form class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"add-owner-form\" method=\"post\">\n     5→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n     6→\n     7→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n     8→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:name}</label>\n     9→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    10→                <div>\n    11→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"firstName\" name=\"firstName\" value=\"{owner.firstName ?: ''}\" />\n    12→\n    13→                </div>\n    14→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    15→                {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null}\n    16→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('firstName')}</span>\n    17→                {/if}\n    18→            </div>\n    19→        </div>\n    20→\n    21→\n    22→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('lastName') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    23→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:last_name}</label>\n    24→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    25→                <div>\n    26→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"lastName\" name=\"lastName\" value=\"{owner.lastName ?: ''}\" />\n    27→\n    28→                </div>\n    29→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    30→                {#if errors.containsKey('lastName') != null}\n    31→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('lastName')}</span>\n    32→                {/if}\n    33→            </div>\n    34→        </div>\n    35→\n    36→\n    37→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    38→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:address}</label>\n    39→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    40→                <div>\n    41→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"address\" name=\"address\" value=\"{owner.address ?: ''}\" />\n    42→\n    43→                </div>\n    44→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    45→                {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null}\n    46→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('address')}</span>\n    47→                {/if}\n    48→            </div>\n    49→        </div>\n    50→\n    51→\n    52→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    53→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:city}</label>\n    54→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    55→                <div>\n    56→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"city\" name=\"city\" value=\"{owner.city ?: ''}\" />\n    57→\n    58→                </div>\n    59→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    60→                {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null}\n    61→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('city')}</span>\n    62→                {/if}\n    63→            </div>\n    64→        </div>\n    65→\n    66→\n    67→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    68→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:telephone}</label>\n    69→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    70→                <div>\n    71→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"telephone\" name=\"telephone\" value=\"{owner.telephone ?: ''}\" />\n    72→\n    73→                </div>\n    74→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    75→                {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null}\n    76→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('telephone')}</span>\n    77→                {/if}\n    78→            </div>\n    79→        </div>\n    80→\n    81→    </div>\n    82→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    83→        <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    84→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">\n    85→                {#if owner}\n    86→                {msg:edit_owner}\n    87→                {#else}\n    88→                {msg:add_owner}\n    89→                {/if}\n    90→            </button>\n    91→        </div>\n    92→    </div>\n    93→</form>\n    94→{/body}\n    95→{/include}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52be45b4-0245-40cb-9c77-3e6f169390e0","uuid":"2da8a952-1e7b-4d43-ada4-8f215f57e6e2"}
